## Design Principles

1. __Consistency__: All components follow the same design language and patterns
2. __Composability__: Components can be easily combined to create more complex UIs
3. __Reusability__: Components are designed to be reused across the application
4. __Accessibility__: Components are built with accessibility in mind
5. __Customization__: Components can be customized through props

When adding new components:

1. Place them in the appropriate category folder
2. Export them from the category's index.ts file
3. Follow the existing naming and code style conventions
4. Include proper TypeScript typing
5. Ensure the component is properly documented
